{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "05a8ca84-6004-413a-b0eb-86ba2fa0fe0d",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "# Common concepts"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "71e95a26-bb34-42a9-ba38-264f0eb121b6",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": [
     "hide-cell"
    ]
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "%load_ext autoreload\n",
    "%autoreload 2\n",
    "\n",
    "from matplotlib import pyplot as plt\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import xplt\n",
    "\n",
    "np.random.seed(4873153)\n",
    "\n",
    "xplt.apply_style()\n",
    "\n",
    "xplt.mpl.rcParams[\"figure.figsize\"] = (3, 2)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "0f7fab2e-8fdd-4658-903b-c67320554b73",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": [
     "hide-cell"
    ]
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "data = xplt.util.AttrDict(\n",
    "    label=\"Data A\",\n",
    "    x=1e-3 * np.random.normal(size=10000),\n",
    "    y=2e-3 * (0.5 + np.random.normal(size=10000)),\n",
    ")\n",
    "data2 = xplt.util.AttrDict(\n",
    "    label=\"Data B\",\n",
    "    x=2e-3 + 3 * data.x,\n",
    "    y=data.y / 2 - 3e-3,\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "53d8e27e-0043-4b53-b8a5-27eee99e1037",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "## Creating plots"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "412fecca-5fc3-4e22-b146-7d342cfb7155",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "All plotting classes share a common API as they are derived either from the base class {class}`XPlot <xplt.base.XPlot>` or {class}`XManifoldPlot <xplt.base.XManifoldPlot>`. In the following we will use the {class}`ParticleHistogramPlot <xplt.particles.ParticleHistogramPlot>` to demonstrate the common concepts."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f1c3ab39-22bb-4cb4-8b3f-a958b14641f9",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "To quickly create a plot, simply instanciate it and provide the data:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "bbf10389-7e30-4c89-bfa5-e726f8a55b88",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 300x200 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plot = xplt.ParticleHistogramPlot(\"x\", particles=data)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "19624b15-1201-49ec-ba39-c1af6836c490",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "The only mandatory parameter is the property to be plotted (`\"x\"`). Most plots also accept a `kind=` parameter to plot different properties on subplots or twin axes.\n",
    "The data provided must contain or be suited to derive the requested properties. See below for a detailed description of properties, units and labels.\n",
    "\n",
    "Most plots allso accept a `mask=` parameter to consider only a subset of the data:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "97a3fcf4-9b43-4e10-859e-b11890e85fc2",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 300x200 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plot = xplt.ParticleHistogramPlot(\"x\", particles=data, mask=data.x < 1e-3)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "4fb553dd-3936-47cb-b6e9-fd5a034f62ca",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Updating plot data"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "25881c3c-4f67-45d6-ab4d-15395e5f879b",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "Plots can also be created blank, and the data updated later. This is very useful to create animations (see {doc}`/examples/animations`):"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "5090aa5a-c344-41e0-ba4e-9f0cfb2f5638",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 300x200 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plot = xplt.ParticleHistogramPlot(\n",
    "    \"x\", bin_width=1e-4, plot_kwargs=dict(label=\"Data A\")\n",
    ")\n",
    "plot.update(data);"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "5b32c282-2d73-474a-b72f-622412bfa826",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "The parameter `plot_kwargs=` always allows to customize the artist.\n",
    "You can add more datasets:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "a2fa9a31-9d0c-4502-8561-449de446adbe",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 300x200 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 6,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plot.add_dataset(\n",
    "    \"ref\",  # optional ID to update data later\n",
    "    particles=data2,\n",
    "    plot_kwargs=dict(label=\"Data B\", c=\"C2\", lw=2),\n",
    "    autoscale=True,\n",
    ")\n",
    "plot.fig"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "5de97f1c-5a2e-4d24-9f84-d6d6434dca06",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "...and update them as needed:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "88fa7365-a2dd-4917-b6e7-37a1a03d7012",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 300x200 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 7,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plot.update(data2, mask=data2.x > 0, dataset_id=\"ref\")\n",
    "plot.fig"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "3634f34e-ef5a-49c2-afbb-85dbf1429377",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "```{tip}\n",
    "To add multiple datasets in a loop, pass `add_default_dataset=False` to the constructor to avoid the default artists from being created for you.\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a0f2e064-6154-4c52-b3a1-9d054dca71fe",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The parameter `autoscale=` of the {meth}`xplt.ParticleHistogramPlot.add_dataset` and {meth}`xplt.ParticleHistogramPlot.update` methods allows to specify the autoscale behaviour. By default, autoscaling is only performed on the first time data is supplied to the plot.  \n",
    "You can also manually autoscale the plot anytime:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "id": "9568533b-1d86-44da-8003-433f36d8eb48",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 300x200 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 8,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plot.autoscale(axis=\"x\", tight=False, reset=True)\n",
    "plot.fig"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "f7318dae-b114-4960-a15c-f50c081802c4",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": []
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "10300366-3a14-48e5-9de0-8325cd7c2f8f",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "### Composing plots"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "d121ce14-45e8-4e1a-bca2-f6f517826a98",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "By passing an existing axis to the constructor, it is possible to create composed plots (the axis shape must match the one otherwise created by the plot):"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "id": "dd8cde66-3b00-4c44-829f-61f8cb07ff38",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 4 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "xplt.mpl.rcParams[\"figure.figsize\"] = (6.4, 4.8)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axs = plt.subplots(2, 2, sharex=\"col\", sharey=\"row\")\n",
    "fig.suptitle(\"A composed plot\")\n",
    "\n",
    "for i, p in enumerate(\"xy\"):\n",
    "    for j, dat in enumerate((data, data2)):\n",
    "        plot = xplt.ParticleHistogramPlot(\n",
    "            p,\n",
    "            dat,\n",
    "            \"count,cumulative\",\n",
    "            ax=axs[:, i],\n",
    "            plot_kwargs=dict(label=dat.label, ls=f\"-{j}\"),  # customization\n",
    "        )\n",
    "        if i == 0:\n",
    "            break\n",
    "\n",
    "for a in axs[:, 1]:\n",
    "    a.set(ylabel=None)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "825e10aa-0a19-4fb5-a06e-4e6779d2be1f",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": []
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ed16530c-1360-44f3-97e0-32be093201a9",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "## Properties, Units and Labels"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "43ba9ed3-993f-4a8d-8ed7-33d1681465ad",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Properties are what makes this library easy to use while still very flexible.\n",
    "\n",
    "A property is anything that we can \"get\" from a dataset, either as an attribute `data.xyz`, an index `data[\"xyz\"]` or even a column in a pandas dataframe.  \n",
    "For brevity, consider the following arbitrary dataset in the following:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "id": "8492a417-24bd-432d-9910-50462f805ca5",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# custom data\n",
    "N = 10000\n",
    "data = {\n",
    "    \"h\": np.linspace(0, 100, num=N),\n",
    "    \"w\": np.random.normal(size=N),\n",
    "    \"x\": np.random.normal(size=N),\n",
    "    \"y\": np.random.normal(size=N),\n",
    "}"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ed969bf7-02c6-41ca-b34a-34592426f31e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Now we can plot the x-y-phasespace simply by specifying exactly that:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "id": "3fc57f50-2886-44b0-8481-5f592576f49a",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 400x400 with 3 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plot = xplt.PhaseSpacePlot(data, \"x-y\", display_units=dict(y=\"m\"))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "0ef8f5f0-a192-422e-8fb1-b3e1d590b013",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "This works, because both `x` and `y` are standard properties which are defined in the library with default settings for units, labels and symbols.\n",
    "Here specifically, the assumption is that `x` is provided in meters since that is the SI unit used by [Xsuite](https://xsuite.readthedocs.io), and that the default display unit for `x` should be millimeters. You can specify a display unit, and the data is automatically converted accordingly."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "049f12e8-6fea-4702-b89d-09d46ec0fa52",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "See below for a list of predefined properties and the default assumed. You can add or change properties and their respective units, labels and symbols if required.\n",
    "Futher, derived properties can easily be defined building on the already existing ones."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "d8900a12-e203-4cb5-a0fe-8c73c1e59b11",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": []
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "2ddd540f-1425-4ef4-98e0-910cb9431e2f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Adding custom data properties"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "18846981-e120-47df-bb71-ab071fc55918",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "To define or overwrite properties of a data object with a certain unit or meaning, you can either register them globally:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "id": "ad08d5aa-934b-45cf-9198-fb2f6f411d0b",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# our data[\"w\"] is the width in km\n",
    "xplt.register_data_property(\"w\", data_unit=\"km\", symbol=\"$w_x$\", description=\"Width\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "c0a01ace-2986-4ac3-a292-5bd7d77e0f91",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "Or on-the-fly for a single plot with the `data_units` parameter.\n",
    "Both enable automatic axes and legend labeling, as well as the use of the `display_units` parameter:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "id": "5b350c6a-5c1a-4418-8389-e2e533ac84f5",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 400x400 with 3 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# our data[\"h\"] is in mm, but we want to convert it to cm\n",
    "plot = xplt.PhaseSpacePlot(\n",
    "    data, \"w-h\", data_units={\"h\": \"mm\"}, display_units={\"h\": \"cm\"}\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "b57f78b9-61de-4e52-a7e9-77417adc4910",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": []
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a7178442-dc93-4e1c-a6d5-d7f7ffade16c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Derived properties"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "50389201-c814-42f9-a943-599798fd61cf",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "It is often useful to add properties that depend on already existing ones,\n",
    "e.g. if you simply want to plot the squareroot of a parameter, or have a complex expression.\n",
    "The function parameters must be valid property names, such that the data and units can be inferred automatically.\n",
    "It is also possible to specify the unit explicitly where necessary."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "id": "d067d612-7440-45f0-ac1c-f87295405486",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# since both x and y are know properties (in meter), A is known to be in square meter\n",
    "xplt.register_derived_property(\"A\", lambda x, y: x * y, description=\"Area\")\n",
    "# since the unit of `6` can not be inferred, we declare B to be in square meter too\n",
    "xplt.register_derived_property(\"B\", lambda A: A + 6, unit=\"m^2\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 15,
   "id": "01861b6c-9865-4f21-855d-fe1b892527fb",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 400x400 with 3 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plot = xplt.PhaseSpacePlot(data, \"A-w\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "35850138-4161-4b35-9f7f-cb06de1124e9",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": []
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "3d559a40-3019-4c25-90fa-93672aefcb27",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "### Default properties"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "158cf9f2-ee0f-41e9-85b0-9f1c0baf6d95",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "Global default properties applicable to all plots:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 16,
   "id": "95970470-7c91-4d01-8b18-6b201dee5cdb",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": [
     "hide-input"
    ]
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/markdown": [
       "| Property       | Unit                                   | Symbol                                  | Description                 | Derived from                 |\n",
       "|:---------------|:---------------------------------------|:----------------------------------------|:----------------------------|:-----------------------------|\n",
       "| `at_turn`      | $  $                                   | $n$                                     | Turn                        |                              |\n",
       "| `charge_ratio` | $  $                                   | $q/q_\\mathrm{ref}$                      | Charge ratio                |                              |\n",
       "| `chi`          | $  $                                   | $(q/q_\\mathrm{ref})/(m/m_\\mathrm{ref})$ | Charge-over-rest-mass ratio |                              |\n",
       "| `count`        | $  $                                   | $N$                                     | Count                       |                              |\n",
       "| `delta`        | $  $                                   | $\\delta$                                |                             |                              |\n",
       "| `energy`       | $ \\mathrm{eV} $                        | $E$                                     | Total energy                |                              |\n",
       "| `m`            | $ \\frac{\\mathrm{eV}}{\\mathrm{c}^{2}} $ | $m$                                     | Rest mass                   | `chi` `charge_ratio` `mass0` |\n",

   "source": [
    "from IPython.display import display, Markdown\n",
    "import pandas\n",
    "import pint\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def get_subclass_names(classname):\n",
    "    all = {classname.__name__: classname}\n",
    "    for subclassname in classname.__subclasses__():\n",
    "        all.update(get_subclass_names(subclassname))\n",
    "    return all\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def display_class_info(cls):\n",
    "    md = \"Additional default properties applicable only to:\"\n",
    "    for name, c in sorted(get_subclass_names(cls).items()):\n",
    "        if name.endswith(\"Plot\") and not \".. deprecated::\" in c.__doc__:\n",
    "            md += f\" {{class}}`{name} <{c.__module__}.{c.__qualname__}>`\\n\"\n",
    "    display(Markdown(md))\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def display_property_info(properties):\n",
    "    der = np.any(\n",
    "        [isinstance(p, xplt.properties.DerivedProperty) for p in properties.values()]\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    df = pandas.DataFrame(columns=[\"Unit\", \"Symbol\", \"Description\", \"Derived from\"])\n",
    "    df.index.name = \"Property\"\n",
    "    for p, prop in sorted(properties.items()):\n",
    "        df.loc[f\"`{p}`\"] = [\n",
    "            f\"$ {pint.Unit(prop.unit):~#L} $\",\n",
    "            prop.symbol,\n",
    "            prop.description or \"\",\n",
    "            (\n",
    "                f\"`{'` `'.join(prop.evaluate.__code__.co_varnames)}`\"\n",
    "                if isinstance(prop, xplt.properties.DerivedProperty)\n",
    "                else \"\"\n",
    "            ),\n",
    "        ]\n",
    "    # https://github.com/jupyter-book/jupyter-book/issues/1501#issuecomment-2301641068\n",
    "    display(Markdown(df.to_markdown()))\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "display_property_info(xplt.properties._default_properties)"
   ]
  },
